### Repro Steps & Context

Currently if I want to install/uninstall multiple packages via [IVsPackageInstaller2](https://github.com/NuGet/NuGet.Client/blob/ba3fa10c1ae0fc4b57f4fa01c8fda0abf47f865a/src/NuGet.Clients/NuGet.VisualStudio/Extensibility/IVsPackageInstaller2.cs) from another VS component then we have to sequentially call install/update/downgrade/uninstall operations 1 by 1 for each package inside each project.
In case we case `n` project and `m` packages in each then it takes `n*m` subsequent calls which is very slow, waste ton of time switching context. Also, some cases it simply fails due to NU1605 error because all involving packages need to be updated same time.
Ideally, we need something like following:

```
public interface IVsPackageInstaller3
{
    void InstallPackages(List<string> sources, Project project, List<PackageIdentity> packageIds, bool ignoreDependencies);
    void InstallPackages(List<string> sources, Project project, List<PackageDependency> packageIds, bool ignoreDependencies);
    void InstallPackages(List<string> sources, Solution solution,  List<(Project project, List<PackageIdentity>packageIds, bool removeDependencies>));
    void InstallPackages(List<string> sources, Solution solution,  List<(Project project, List<PackageDependency>packageIds, bool removeDependencies>));
}
```

```
public interface IVsPackageUninstaller
{
    void UninstallPackages(Project project, List<string>packageIds, bool removeDependencies);
    void UninstallPackages(Solution solution, List<(Project project, List<string>packageIds, bool removeDependencies>));
}
```

